<h3>Auto Loaded Video Parameters with Day/Night Switch</h3>
<blockquote>
  <p>Some video parameters should be concerned to be the part of the video parameters in Night Time Profile but not in the above list. These parameters could be managed automatically by firmware. So, it does not need to have user intervention. Or, these parameters have two settings for DAY and NIGHT time mode already. Here gives the description of these parameters.</p>
  <p><strong><u>WDR (Wide Dynamic Range)</u></strong></p>
  <blockquote>
    <p>There are two settings of WDR levels in the WDR configurations. Please refer to VIDEO_WDR URL in ENCODER CGI. The firmware loads the day time WDR level in day time and loads the night time WDR level in night time automatically.</p>
  </blockquote>
  <p><strong><u>DNR (Digital Noise Reduction)</u></strong></p>
  <blockquote>
    <p>This function was disabled all the time. No difference in this parameter for day/night time mode.</p>
  </blockquote>
  <p><strong><u>BLC (Back Light Compensation)</u></strong></p>
  <blockquote>
    <p>Currently, it deos not show penefit to have two settings for day/night video management. It keeps one setting for all the time.</p>
  </blockquote>
  <p><strong><u>Black Level Extension</u></strong></p>
  <blockquote>
    <p>This function is only available in the PlatformT video server which is not a day/night capable camera. We don't concern it as the video parameter in night time video profile.</p>
  </blockquote>
</blockquote>
